canonical:
  title: 書天壽僧院壁
  author: 李仁老
  language: lzh
  text: 待客客未到尋僧僧亦無唯餘林外鳥欵曲勸提壺
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 書天壽僧院壁
  author: 李仁老
  language: lzh
  text: 待客客未到。尋僧僧亦無。唯餘林外鳥。欵曲勸提壺。
korean:
  title: 서 천수승원벽
  author: 이인로
  language: kor
  text: |-
    손을 기다리매 손이 오지 않고
    중을 찾으니 중이 또한 없구나
    오직 수풀 밖의 새만 남아서
    관곡히 술 들기를 권하네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0170&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 술 들기[提壺] : '
    value: 새 이름이므로 술병을 이끌고 오라고 권한다는 뜻이다.
english:
  title: Written on the Wall of Cheonsu Monastery
  author: Lee In-ro
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I await guests, but guests do not come.
    I seek monks, yet monks are nowhere to be found.
    Only the birds beyond the grove remain—
    They gently urge me to raise the wine cup.
  footnotes:
    - 提壺 (tí-hú), literally 'raise the pot,' is a type of bird whose name became a playful reference to bringing wine. The speaker personifies the birds as gentle companions urging him to drink in the absence of human guests and monks.
